	     Cairo - An angry Egyptian President Abdel Fattah al-Sisi pledged to respond with "brutal force" against militants who massacred at least 235 people at a mosque during weekly prayers on Friday. "The army and police will avenge our martyrs and return security and stability with force in the coming short period," he also said in a televised speech. 24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.  